# Issue commit linking

Every **task-related** commit must reference a GitHub issue so the **Development** panel links correctly and the issue auto-closes on merge to `main`.

## Required subject format

```
<type>(<scope>)[#N]: <imperative summary>
```

| Part | Rule |
|---|---|
| `<type>` | Conventional Commits: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `ci`, `build`, `perf` |
| `<scope>` | Allowed scopes from `01-git-workflow.mdc` |
| `[#N]` | **Mandatory** on task commits |
| Summary | Imperative mood; whole subject ≤72 chars |

## Required body format

```
fixes #N
```

Place on its own line in the commit body. Multiple issues: one per line.

## Epic (parent Feature) issues

| Commit | Subject | Body |
|---|---|---|
| Any subtask | `[#<leaf>]` | `fixes #<leaf>` |
| **Final** child of parent P | `[#<leaf>]` | `fixes #<leaf>` + `fixes #<P>` per parent in `CLOSE_PARENTS` |
| Atomic leaf | `[#<leaf>]` | `fixes #<leaf>` |

**Do not** put `fixes #<epic>` on intermediate subtasks.

Orchestrator passes `CLOSE_PARENTS: [#P, …]` or `none` in execution prompts. Execution agents **must not guess**.

## Examples

```bash
# GOOD — intermediate subtask under epic #8
feat(auth)[#11]: add GitHub OAuth callback handler

fixes #11

# GOOD — last in-scope child of epic #8
feat(auth)[#12]: add refresh token rotation

fixes #12
fixes #8

# BAD — premature epic close
feat(auth)[#11]: add OAuth callback

fixes #11
fixes #8
```

## Auto-close on merge

GitHub auto-closes issues with `fixes #N` in commit body when merged to `main` (default branch).

## Exceptions (no issue key required)

- Pure repo hygiene: `chore(repo): init pnpm workspace` (rare)
- Integration merge commits: `chore(repo)[#N]: integrate orchestrator batch (<BATCH_ID>)`
